class Solution {
public:
    string breakPalindrome(string palindrome) {
        int n = palindrome.size();
        if (n == 1) return "";
        string res = palindrome;
        for (int i = 0; i < n / 2; i++) {
            if (res[i] != 'a') {
                res[i] = 'a';
                return res;
            }
        }
        res[n - 1] = 'b';
        return res;
    }
};
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: We iterate through the first half of the palindrome, replacing the first non-'a' character with 'a'. If all characters are 'a', we replace the last character with 'b' to make it not a palindrome. This approach ensures the resulting string is lexicographically smallest.

